    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD RECONDITIONING
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CYLINDER HEAD RECONDITIONING</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="5">
            <title>NOZZLE SLEEVE REPLACEMENT</title>
            <svcprocinfo>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>REPLACE THE NOZZLE SLEEVE ONLY IF LEAKAGE IS PRESENT.</para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Use nozzle sleeve remover ZTSE2587A (Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050422">4.22</hotlnk>).
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </svcprocinfo>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the nozzle sleeve puller adapter (
                    <emph type="bold">ZT 206437</emph>) into the sleeve to be removed. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050423">4.23</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>This tool grips the nozzle sleeve by threading into it. Start the adapter into the nozzle
                            sleeve by striking it with a hammer. Then screw the nozzle sleeve puller adapter into the
                            sleeve using a wrench.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect a slide hammer (
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE1879</emph>) to the adapter and pull the sleeve from its bore. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050424">4.24</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discard the sleeve.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the nozzle bore at the top and bottom using a rotary wire brush
                    <emph type="bold">(ZTSE4394</emph>). Blow out with filtered compressed air.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050422" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1675" filename="../figeg1/EG1675.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.22.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050423" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1677" filename="../figeg1/EG1677.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.23.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050424" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1676" filename="../figeg1/EG1676.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.24.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Loctite(r) 262 or equivalent to the nozzle sleeve contact points (2 places). Refer
                    to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050425">4.25</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the nozzle sleeve using the nozzle sleeve installer
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE2534A</emph>. Drive the sleeve until it bottoms in the bore. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050426">4.26</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If performing a nozzle sleeve installation in chassis, be sure to drain the coolant before
                            replacing the nozzle sleeves in chassis. When installing nozzle sleeves in chassis, piston
                            should be bottom dead center or installation tool may contact piston.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef1050425" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1679" filename="../figeg1/EG1679.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.25.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050426" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1678" filename="../figeg1/EG1678.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.26.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
